HEADWORD: Tercine
<hw>Ter"cine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from L.
<ets>tertius</ets> the third.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A cellular
layer derived from the nucleus of an ovule and surrounding the embryo
sac. Cf. <er>Quintine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
